  "prompt": "How did you first find out about your sexuality?",
  "response": "Discovering one's sexuality is usually a gradual and personal process. Many people first realize their sexual orientation through feelings of attraction or crushes during adolescence. This might happen when they notice how they feel towards characters in movies, celebrities, or peers. It can also come from introspection and understanding how these feelings differ from societal norms or expectations. Ultimately, the journey is unique for everyone and can involve a lot of reflection and exploration.",
